          "back": "طبيب",
          "romanized": "tabib",
          "grammarNote": "Arabic profession nouns are masculine by default. Feminine is formed by adding ة (ta marbuta): طبيب → طبيبة (tabib → tabiba = female doctor), مهندس → مهندسة (muhandis → muhandisa = female engineer). Unlike Spanish, Arabic doesn't drop the article when saying 'I am a doctor': أنا طبيب (ana tabib = I am a doctor)."
