    "to_like_to_enjoy": {
      "levels": [
        {
          "front": "To like / To enjoy",
          "back": "يحب / يستمتع",
          "romanized": "yuhibb / yastamti'",
          "grammarNote": "Arabic 'يحب' (yuhibb = to love/like) is used where Spanish uses 'gustar'. The structure is direct: أحب القراءة (uhibb al-qira'a = I like reading), هي تحب الغناء (hiya tuhibb al-ghina' = she likes singing). Unlike Spanish gustar, the subject of the Arabic sentence is the person, not the thing liked."
        },
